b'Huggies:registered: is truly thankful for our founding partnership with @diapernetwork and the 200+ member diaper banks that help support families in need across the US. Each of the member diaper banks are an important part of the communities they serve.
 
@westsidebabysea has been providing essentials for families in need in the Seattle, WA area since 2001, and they are a member of The National Diaper Bank Network. So far this year, the WestSide Baby team has distributed 2 million+ diapers to their community.  With #HelpingHugs, they help to support ensuring every child has the basic essentials to thrive. 

Thank you WestSide Baby team and all of the NDBN member diaper banks for your dedication, passion and service to your community. Huggies:registered: is proud to support you. :red_heart_selector:
.
#HelpingHugs #diaperbank #diaperneed #diaperneedawareness'

b'There\xe2\x80\x99s nothing like holding your NICU baby for the first time. Did you know that 400,000 babies are born preterm each year (prior to 37 weeks gestation)? Moms and Dads of premature babies are more likely to develop short term and long term mental health challenges as a result. Huggies:registered: proudly sponsors @handtohold to make virtual support services free for all NICU families who need it. Hand to Hold is a nonprofit 501(c)3 that provides powerful resources and support to families before, during and after a NICU stay. :baby::red_heart_selector:
.
#HelpingHugs #WorldPrematurityDay #prematurityawareness

b'Huggies is honored to feature Sam, a 2-year old Little Mover that makes everyone\xe2\x80\x99s day a little brighter.  Sam has come so far from being born at 25 weeks and weighing 1 lb 4 oz.  Today Sam is a happy, thriving toddler who loves playing with his brother and sister and pushing the limits on his walker. \xe2\x80\x9cRaising a child with special needs does not take a special family\xe2\x80\xa6it\xe2\x80\x99s what makes a family so special. Sam has turned our world into a place of compassion, empathy, joy and hope.\xe2\x80\x9d -Sara E, Sam\xe2\x80\x99s Mom.
.
October is Down Syndrome Awareness Month. Did you know that most individuals with Down Syndrome have low muscle tone (hypotonia) which is why it takes them longer to learn how to stand, walk, talk and eat the same food as others?  They work extra hard and with the help of therapy they get there in their own time. :raising_hands: :blue_heart: :yellow_heart: The Huggies team celebrates Sam and all special needs children and their families.
.
IG: @saraengland1
#Downsyndromeawarenessmonth #Downsyndromeawareness #HuggOn'

b'Huggies:registered: is honored to share this story. This is Ethan (age 5) and his mom, Gabby. When Ethan was 6 months old, Gabby needed food stamps and WIC but there wasn\xe2\x80\x99t federal assistance for diapers (and still isn\xe2\x80\x99t). Gabby was fortunate to have a support system that could help bridge the gap for her family but this isn\xe2\x80\x99t the situation for all families in need. It wasn\xe2\x80\x99t long before Gabby got back on her feet and then began volunteering at the @MiamiDiaperBank and shortly after she was offered a full time position. Gabby is now leading the @Miamidiaperbank as Executive Director and her son is learning all about helping his community. The Miami Diaper bank is a member of @Nationaldiaperbanknetwork. Gabby and her team have distributed 1.2 Million diapers, 200,000 baby wipes and 50,000 articles of clothing during this pandemic. Thank you Gabby & Ethan, for sharing your story and inspiring the Huggies:registered: team! We are proud to be a supporter! #helpinghugs'

b'It\xe2\x80\x99s #DiaperNeedAwareness week! Little Essentials (@lehelps) is a NYC area nonprofit and one of the 200+ members of @diapernetwork. They have been distributing essentials to NYC families for 10 years and serve an average of 160 families a month. Diapers and hygiene items have been the most requested items for families here during the COVID-19 pandemic and this team has distributed 120,000+ diapers since March to families in need.  Thank you Little Essentials team for the #HelpingHugs that you provide for your community. Huggies:registered: is proud to be a supporter!'

b'You never know what someone else is going through.\n\nHuggies is proud to be the founding sponsor of @diapernetwork a non-profit who with their 200+ member diaper banks help families that are struggling with the basic need of clean, dry diapers for their children. Join us in helping bring awareness to Diaper Need and learn how you can help. b'As most of you know, Hurricane Laura has had a big impact on families and their ability to access essentials, like diapers. Huggies:registered:  just sent 100,000 diapers to support  @diapernetwork and their member diaper banks in Louisiana to help families in need.\n.\nHere are two enthusiastic community volunteers from New Orleans! These two boys have been helping out their Mom at @juniorleagueno, which is a member diaper bank of The National Diaper Bank Network.  Her boys are learning through age appropriate volunteering and giving #HelpingHugs to their community. Did you know that half of the National Diaper Bank Network diaper banks are completely volunteer run? All diaper banks need volunteers, and Junior League of New Orleans is no exception, as they rely on assistance from their communities to help those in need. It\xe2\x80\x99s awesome to see helpers of all ages learning to volunteer!'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cOn April 15th, I should have been taking my 1st family trip to run the marathon in Boston. Instead, after the marathon was cancelled I found myself still running at 5am and thinking of some way I could give back to the workers who were doing their own kind of marathon every single day - a marathon they could not have possibly prepared for. My heart ached for the people who had lost their jobs, the small business owners, the nurses, doctors and healthcare workers. I put an idea out to my local running group and community to cater a meal for some healthcare workers at a Hospital in NJ- and the running community LITERALLY delivered!! In total we raised $1,200 for and donated 136 meals. And I still ran my marathon! 26.2 miles on local roads near my home raising money for the homeless youth I work with at Covenant House. And my son was waiting for me with the biggest hug at the finish line.\xe2\x80\x9d Jacqueline M.\n.\nThe small things continue to be the big things right now. We continue to be inspired by kindness. Thank you for your moments of care, empathy, and compassion. Continue to share your #HelpingHugs moments to keep it going! #runnermom #marathon #marathonmom #runningcommunity #runhappy'

b'"During labor, my baby\xe2\x80\x99s umbilical cord burst, which triggered an emergency c-section. My daughter didn\xe2\x80\x99t have a heartbeat for 13 minutes. It was a blanket of silence while the amazing Neonatal team worked to save her. I heard, \xe2\x80\x98we have a heartbeat\xe2\x80\x99 and saw the top of her little head as they rushed her away. I remember my husband asking \xe2\x80\x98Will she be OK?\xe2\x80\x99 and the nurse replied, 'We\xe2\x80\x99ll let you know as soon as we can.'
We brought her home 29 days later with a dialysis tube, bags of medication and a strict schedule. Cry, pray, laugh, repeat. It felt like forever. I cannot imagine our NICU journey without grandparents and friends who stood in the gap for us. Watching our son, making meals, walking the dog, and most of all, hugging us close when we were broken, scared and tired.
Working from home these past weeks, I have that same baby sitting next to me every day. A thriving 9-year old who can push me to my limits. Even on my worst mom days, I couldn\xe2\x80\x99t be more thankful.
Looking back, I realize how much our NICU stay changed us forever. It challenged, softened and strengthened us. It\xe2\x80\x99s the reason I feel immediate connection with other NICU moms. They truly \xe2\x80\x98get\xe2\x80\x99 it. And it\xe2\x80\x99s why Huggies partnership with Hand to Hold means so much to me personally. These families need a hand to hold more than ever. If that\xe2\x80\x99s you today, know this mom is holding you close. Hang in there."
.
Huggies is partnering with @handtohold as part of their #HelpingHugs program to help NICU families get the support they need before, during and after a NICU stay. Free virtual support services are now in place - see link in bio.'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cWe went in for my wife\xe2\x80\x99s first ultrasound. The tech said, "yeah, there are definitely two in there." Guys, I was like\xe2\x80\xa6 two what? Two hands? Two legs? Are you freakin kidding me TWINS!?
.
Fast forward 5 months for a routine check-up. The Doctor tells my wife that the babies are no longer thriving. They were going to monitor her, and we wouldn\xe2\x80\x99t be going home. I\xe2\x80\x99ll never forget the NICU Doctor telling me that babies born that early usually have a 20% chance they won\xe2\x80\x99t make it their first year.
.
We cried. We prayed. But a week later, it was time. At 11:55 and 11:59am my wife gave birth to Selma (1lbs 15oz) and Hector (1lbs 11oz.) They could wrap their whole hand around the last joint on my pinky finger.
.
Looking back, we were a wreck. But, Hector and Selma just recently turned 3 and are kicking butt and kicking our butts too! I cannot imagine our 71-day stay in the NICU without access to help when we were worried and scared."
.
Huggies is partnering with Hand to Hold to help NICU families get the support they need before, during, and after a NICU stay. Free NICU virtual support services are now in place. Learn more at the link in bio.
.
#HelpingHugs #NICU #NICUsupport #virtualsupport #NICUdad #NICUbaby #preemie #preemiedad #nicugraduate #nicuwarrior #twins'

b'"Tonight my neighbor (who I don\xe2\x80\x99t know very well) called me on my way to work in the ER. He said, \'I know you\xe2\x80\x99ve been working really hard and doing it all on your own. I appreciate all that you\xe2\x80\x99re doing. I\xe2\x80\x99d like to rake your yard for you next week.\xe2\x80\x99 I burst into tears of gratitude from this incredibly kind gesture. It was hard to say yes. But I did...for both of us. I\xe2\x80\x99m exhausted and scared and lonely. Yet, I hold steadfast all of the beauty, grace, selflessness, and love I see in others daily.\xe2\x80\x9d - Megan M., RN. Single mom of 2 boys.\n\nWe have been inspired by this story of kindness and would love to hear more. Share a story of kindness that you\xe2\x80\x99ve received using the hashtag #HelpingHugs to help spread some positivity. Because right now, the small things are the big things.'
